# Layout Spacing Standards

These are the canonical spacing values for the app shell. Every page and content component must respect them.

## Reference Anatomy

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Sidebar (left)  │  Avatar bar (64 px / h-16)    │
│                  ├───────────────────────────────-│
│                  │← 32 px padding-left (px-8)    →│
│                  │                                │
│                  │  ↕ 24 px gap below top bar     │
│                  │                                │
│                  │  Title bar (TitleBar) / Content    │
│                  │                                │
└──────────────────┴───────────────────────────────-┘
```

## Spacing Values

| Relationship                              | Value    | Tailwind class | Notes                                  |
| ----------------------------------------- | -------- | -------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Below top bar → first content element     | **24 px** | `pt-6`         | Applied on the content wrapper div     |
| Left edge (from sidebar) → content        | **32 px** | `px-8`         | Horizontal padding on Avatar bar, Top bar & content |
| Avatar bar height                         | **64 px** | `h-16`         | Fixed; do not change                   |

## Implementation Rules

1. **Below the avatar bar**: The inner `<div>` inside `<main>` that wraps the page `<TitleBar />` should use `pt-6` (24 px) top padding so there is consistent space between the avatar bar and the title bar (see `src/app/page.tsx`).

   **Main column background:** The shell uses a flat **`neutral-50`** fill (via `AppGroovedMainColumn`); no line-field overlay on the page. The **left sidebar** uses **`SidebarLineFieldPattern`** (horizontal line field only on the nav). Pages use the normal **`pt-6`** wrapper before `TitleBar` (same as Staff / Customers).

2. **From the sidebar (left padding)**: All content inside the main column uses `px-8` (32 px) horizontal padding. This applies to `<AvatarBar>`, the page-level `<TitleBar>`, and `<main>` content containers.

3. **Do not nest these paddings.** The `TitleBar` component already carries `px-8`. Child content sections that sit inside `<main>` should also use `px-8` individually (not inherit it from a parent wrapper that double-pads).

## Current Implementation Reference

Matches `src/app/page.tsx` (inside `AppGroovedMainColumn`):

```tsx
<AvatarBar />
<main className="flex flex-1 flex-col overflow-hidden">
  <div className="flex flex-1 flex-col min-h-0 overflow-hidden pt-6">
    <TitleBar breadcrumbs={…} title={…} right={…} />
    {/* …page body; use px-8 where needed */}
  </div>
</main>
```

`pt-6` is the 24px gap **below the avatar bar** and **above** the page `TitleBar`.

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Gap between the avatar bar and the page `TitleBar` is exactly 24 px (`pt-6` on the page wrapper).
- [ ] Horizontal padding from sidebar edge is exactly 32 px (`px-8`).
- [ ] Avatar bar height remains 64 px (`h-16`).
- [ ] New page components do not introduce extra top/left padding that compounds with these values.
